class  ServiceThread
 Class ServiceThread is used to implement services, i.e. tasks which perform permanent background activity like network services. A service thread does not need any graphical user interface but needs to run as an own thread. It only always awakes from idle when it receives a message or when a timer expires. To handle the message overwrite method OnMessage(). For an automated start-up and shut-down of the service thread use class ServiceThreadStarter. More...

#define APOXI_TRACE
 

Three trace levels can be defined at compile time: APOXI_TRACE: Tracing is enabled, no Level 2 and 3 trace; enabled by default APOXI_TRACE_LEVEL_2: Tracer-Classes and Level2-Classes generate output APOXI_TRACE_LEVEL_3: Tracer-Classes, Level2- and Level3-Classes generate output

APOXI_TRACE_MEM: Only memory allocation and deallocation is traced

On default tracing level 1 is enabled (APOXI_TRACE). The switch APOXI_TRACE_DISABLED will disable tracing when set.

Function Documentation

template<class DestClassPointer>
void CastMsg (  DestClassPointer &  dest_msg,
const Message *  src_msg
)  [inline]
 

Function template CastMsg is used to downcast a pointer to a Message class to a pointer to some Message derived class. It supports casting of both pointers to non-const and pointers to const messages. Note, a pointer to a const Message will automatically be casted to a pointer to a non-const Message derived class in case it is needed! Hence, this function template is not const correct.
